The thing about integrated office suites is that inevitably you don't need all of the features they provide, or at least you use some of them less than others. New research from managed services provider Ensono shows that 83 percent of enterprises say Microsoft 365 is an invaluable part of their business operations. However, almost half aren't using all of the features available. More significantly a worrying proportion are neglecting the cybersecurity features available, leaving them open to vulnerabilities. The survey shows that 38 percent are not using multi-factor authentication (MFA), only 43 percent have Conditional Access Controls (CAC) in&#8230; <a href="https://betanews.com/2022/01/25/almost-half-organizations-dont-use-all-microsoft-365-features/" rel="nofollow">[Continue Reading]</a>